The next simplest form is a single proper Interval <T> (i.e. normal two-sided or half-open interval). The most complex form is a list of any combination of point and proper intervals.

P_C_TERMINOLOGY_CODE.name: P_C_TERMINOLOGY_CODE
P_C_TERMINOLOGY_CODE.description:
Constrainer type for instances of TERMINOLOGY_CODE. The primary expression of the constraint is in the property `tuple_constraint', and comes in 3 variations:
* a single at-code
* a single ac-code, representing a value-set that is defined in the archetype terminology
* a list of at- and/or ac-codes, representing the possibilities of a tuple constraint
The last possibility above is enabled by the merge_tuple routine, which enables the constraint of another single-valued C_TERMINOLOGY_CODE to be merged with the current one.

P_C_TEMPORAL.name: P_C_TEMPORAL
P_C_TEMPORAL.description: Purpose Abstract parent of C_ORDERED types whose base type is an ISO date/time type.

pattern_constraint.name: pattern_constraint
pattern_constraint.description: Optional alternative constraint in the form of a pattern based on ISO8601. See descendants for details.

P_C_TIME.name: P_C_TIME
P_C_TIME.description: ISO 8601-compatible constraint on instances of Time in the form either of a set of validity values, or else date ranges based on the C_ORDERED list constraint. There is no validity flag for ‘hour’, since it must always be by definition mandatory in order to have a sensible time at all. Syntax expressions of instances of this class include “HH:??:xx” (time with optional minutes and seconds not allowed).

P_C_DATE.name: P_C_DATE
P_C_DATE.description: ISO 8601-compatible constraint on instances of Date in the form either of a set of validity values, or else date ranges based on the C_ORDERED list constraint. There is no validity flag for ‘year’, since it must always be by definition mandatory in order to have a sensible date at all. Syntax expressions of instances of this class include “YYYY-??-??” (date with optional month and day).

P_C_DATE_TIME.name: P_C_DATE_TIME
P_C_DATE_TIME.description: ISO 8601-compatible constraint on instances of Date_Time. There is no validity flag for ‘year’, since it must always be by definition mandatory in order to have a sensible date/time at all. Syntax expressions of instances of this class include “YYYY-MM-DDT??:??:??” (date/time with optional time) and “YYYY-MMDDTHH:MM:xx” (date/time, seconds not allowed).

P_ARCHETYPE.name: P_ARCHETYPE
P_ARCHETYPE.description:
Archetype equivalent to ARCHETYPED class in Common reference model. Defines semantics of identfication, lifecycle, versioning, composition and specialisation.

An archetype is a modelled as a particular kind of AUTHORED_RESOURCE, and as such, includes descriptive meta-data, language information and revision history. The ARCHETYPE class adds identifying information, a definition - expressed in terms of constraints on instances of an object model, and an ontology.

parent_archetype_id.name: parent_archetype_id
parent_archetype_id.description: Identifier of the specialisation parent of this archetype.

is_differential.name: is_differential
is_differential.description: Flag indicating whether this archetype is differential or flat in its contents. Top-level source archetypes have this flag set to True.

definition.name: definition
definition.description: Root node of the definition of this archetype.

rules.name: rules
rules.description: Rules relating to this archetype. Statements are expressed in first order predicate logic, and usually refer to at least two attributes.

P_AUTHORED_ARCHETYPE.name: P_AUTHORED_ARCHETYPE
P_AUTHORED_ARCHETYPE.description: Root object of a standalone, authored archetype, including all meta-data, description, other identifiers and lifecycle.

adl_version.name: adl_version
adl_version.description: ADL version if archteype was read in from an ADL sharable archetype.

build_uid.name: build_uid
build_uid.description: Unique identifier of this archetype artefact instance. A new identifier is assigned every time the content is changed by a tool. Used by tools to distinguish different revisions and/or interim snapshots of the same artefact.

rm_release.name: rm_release
rm_release.description: Semver.org compatible release of the most recent reference model release on which the archetype in its current version is based. This does not imply conformance only to this release, since an archetype may be valid with respect to multiple releases of a reference model.

is_generated.name: is_generated
is_generated.description: If True, indicates that this artefact was machine-generated from some other source, in which case, tools would expect to overwrite this artefact on a new generation. Editing tools should set this value to False when a user starts to manually edit an archetype.

P_TEMPLATE.name: P_TEMPLATE
P_TEMPLATE.description: Class representing source template, i.e. a kind of archetype that may include template overlays, and may be restricted by tools to only defining mandations, prohibitions, and restrictions on elements already defined in the flat parent.

P_OPERATIONAL_TEMPLATE.name: P_OPERATIONAL_TEMPLATE
P_OPERATIONAL_TEMPLATE.description:
Root object of an operational template. An operational template is derived from a TEMPLATE definition and the ARCHETYPEs and/or TEMPLATE_OVERLAYs mentioned by that template by a process of flattening, and potentially removal of unneeded languages and terminologies.

An operational template is used for generating and validating canonical openEHR data, and also as a source artefact for generating other downstream technical artefacts, including XML schemas, APIs and UI form definitions.

component_terminologies.name: component_terminologies
component_terminologies.description: Compendium of flattened terminologies of archetypes externally referenced from this archetype, keyed by archetype identifier. This will almost always be present in a template.

terminology_extracts.name: terminology_extracts
terminology_extracts.description: Directory of term definitions as a two-level  table. The outer hash keys are term codes,  e.g. "at4", and the inner hash key are term  attribute names, e.g. "text", "description" etc.

P_ARCHETYPE_HRID.name: P_ARCHETYPE_HRID
P_ARCHETYPE_HRID.description: Human_readable identifier (HRID) for an archetype or template.

rm_publisher.name: rm_publisher
rm_publisher.description: Name of the Reference Model publisher.

rm_package.name: rm_package
rm_package.description: Name of the package in whose reachability graph the rm_class class is found (there can be more than one possibility in many reference models).

rm_class.name: rm_class
rm_class.description: Name of the root class of this archetype.

concept_id.name: concept_id
concept_id.description: The short concept name of the archetype as used in the multi-axial archetype_hrid.

release_version.name: release_version
release_version.description: The full numeric version of this archetype consisting of 3 parts, e.g. 1.8.2. The archetype_hrid feature includes only the major version.

version_status.name: version_status
version_status.description: The status of the version, i.e. released, release_candidate etc.

build_count.name: build_count
build_count.description: The build count since last increment of any version part.

P_AUTHORED_RESOURCE.name: P_AUTHORED_RESOURCE
P_AUTHORED_RESOURCE.description: Abstract idea of an online resource created by a human author.

original_language.name: original_language
original_language.description: Language in which this resource was initially authored. Although there is no language primacy of resources overall, the language of original authoring is required to ensure natural language translations can preserve quality. Language is relevant in both the description and ontology sections.

is_controlled.name: is_controlled
is_controlled.description: True if this resource is under any kind of change control (even file copying), in which case revision history is created.

translations.name: translations
translations.description: List of details for each natural translation made of this resource, keyed by language. For each translation listed here, there must be corresponding sections in all language-dependent parts of the resource. The original_language does not appear in this list.

description.name: description
description.description: Description and lifecycle information of the resource.

uid.name: uid
uid.description: Unique identifier of the family of archetypes having the same interface identifier (same major version).

annotations.name: annotations
annotations.description: Annotations on individual items within the resource, keyed by path. The inner table takes the form of a Hash table of String values keyed by String tags.

term_definitions.name: term_definitions
term_definitions.description:
Directory of term definitions as a two-level 
table. The outer hash keys are term codes, 
e.g. "at0004", and the inner hash key are term 
attribute names, e.g. "text", "description" etc.

term_bindings.name: term_bindings
term_bindings.description:
Directory of term bindings as a two-level 
table. The outer hash keys are local term codes, 
e.g. "at0004", and the inner hash keys are terminology 
code phrases, e.g. "SNOMED(2003)::163034007" etc.

obsolete-elom.name: obsolete-elom
obsolete-elom.description: Assertions are expressed in archetypes in typed first-order predicate logic (FOL). They are used in two places: to express archetype slot constraints, and to express invariants in complex object constraints. In both of these places, their role is to constrain something inside the archetype. Constraints on external resources such as terminologies are expressed in the constraint binding part of the archetype ontology.

EL_TYPE_DEF.name: EL_TYPE_DEF
EL_TYPE_DEF.description: Ancestor class for type definitions known in the openEHR Expression formalism.

type_name.name: type_name
type_name.description: Natural language type name of this type as used in abstract rules syntax variable declarations.

type_anchor.name: type_anchor
type_anchor.description: Attribute of the openEHR primitive type (or Any) corresponding to this type definition meta-type.

TYPE_DEF_BOOLEAN.name: TYPE_DEF_BOOLEAN
TYPE_DEF_BOOLEAN.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Boolean.

TYPE_DEF_DATE.name: TYPE_DEF_DATE
TYPE_DEF_DATE.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Date.

TYPE_DEF_DATE_TIME.name: TYPE_DEF_DATE_TIME
TYPE_DEF_DATE_TIME.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Date_time.

TYPE_DEF_DURATION.name: TYPE_DEF_DURATION
TYPE_DEF_DURATION.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Duration.

TYPE_DEF_INTEGER.name: TYPE_DEF_INTEGER
TYPE_DEF_INTEGER.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Integer.

TYPE_DEF_OBJECT_REF.name: TYPE_DEF_OBJECT_REF
TYPE_DEF_OBJECT_REF.description: Rules meta-type representing the type Object_ref, which is assumed to by the type of any non-primitive reference target within a rule.

TYPE_DEF_REAL.name: TYPE_DEF_REAL
TYPE_DEF_REAL.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Real.

TYPE_DEF_STRING.name: TYPE_DEF_STRING
TYPE_DEF_STRING.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type String.

TYPE_DEF_TERMINOLOGY_CODE.name: TYPE_DEF_TERMINOLOGY_CODE
TYPE_DEF_TERMINOLOGY_CODE.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Terminology_code.

TYPE_DEF_TIME.name: TYPE_DEF_TIME
TYPE_DEF_TIME.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Time.

TYPE_DEF_URI.name: TYPE_DEF_URI
TYPE_DEF_URI.description: Rules meta-type representing the primitive type Uri.

FUNCTION_DEF_EXAMPLE.name: FUNCTION_DEF_EXAMPLE
FUNCTION_DEF_EXAMPLE.description:
Example of an externally defined function of signature:

    func (v: Numeric): Numeric

FUNCTION_DEF_EXTERNAL.name: FUNCTION_DEF_EXTERNAL
FUNCTION_DEF_EXTERNAL.description: Ancestor class of externally defined function types.

OP_DEF_AND.name: OP_DEF_AND
OP_DEF_AND.description: Illustrative class showing what the normally built-in logical 'and' operator looks like as an external definition.

OP_DEF_EXAMPLE.name: OP_DEF_EXAMPLE
OP_DEF_EXAMPLE.description: Example custom operator definition as a class, for an operator whose identifier is 'xxx' and for which the symbols "xxx" and "%" can be used, and with a two-argument numeric signature.

OP_DEF_EXISTS.name: OP_DEF_EXISTS
OP_DEF_EXISTS.description: Illustrative class showing what the normally built-in logical 'exists' operator looks like as an external definition.

OPERATOR_DEF_EXTERNAL.name: OPERATOR_DEF_EXTERNAL
OPERATOR_DEF_EXTERNAL.description: Ancestor of concrete operator definition types. Adds an optional execution agent, typically implemented by closures / lambdas/ agents in languages supporting functional programming.

BMM_MODEL_ACCESS.name: BMM_MODEL_ACCESS
BMM_MODEL_ACCESS.description: Access to BMM models that have been loaded and validated from one or more schema sets.

schema_directories.name: schema_directories
schema_directories.description: List of directories where all the schemas loaded here are found.

all_schemas.name: all_schemas
all_schemas.description: All schemas found and loaded from `_schema_directory_`. Keyed by `_schema_id_`.

bmm_models.name: bmm_models
bmm_models.description: Top-level (root) models in use, keyed by `_model_id_`.

matching_bmm_models.name: matching_bmm_models
matching_bmm_models.description: Validated models, keyed by `_model_id()_` and any shorter forms of id, with some or no versioning information. For example, the keys `"openEHR_EHR_1.0.4"`, `"openEHR_EHR_1.0"`, `"openEHR_EHR_1"`, and `"openEHR_EHR"` will all match the `"openEHR_EHR_1.0.4"` model, assuming it is the most recent version available.

BMM_SCHEMA_DESCRIPTOR.name: BMM_SCHEMA_DESCRIPTOR
BMM_SCHEMA_DESCRIPTOR.description: Descriptor for a BMM schema. Contains a meta-data table of attributes obtained from a mini-ODIN parse of the  schema file.

meta_data.name: meta_data
meta_data.description: Table of `{key, value}` of schema meta-data, keys are string values defined by `{BMM_DEFINITIONS}.Metadata_*` constants.

includes.name: includes
includes.description: Identifiers of schemas included by this schema.

BMM_SCHEMA.name: BMM_SCHEMA
BMM_SCHEMA.description: Abstract parent of any persistable form of a BMM model, e.g. `P_BMM_SCHEMA`.

bmm_version.name: bmm_version
bmm_version.description: Version of BMM model, enabling schema evolution reasoning. Persisted attribute.

includes.name: includes
includes.description:
Inclusion list of any form of BMM model, in the form of a hash of individual include specifications, each of which at least specifies the id of another schema, and may specify a namespace via which types from the included schemas are known in this schema.
Persisted attribute.

model_name.name: model_name
model_name.description: Name of this model, if this schema is a model root point. Not set for sub-schemas that are not considered models on their own.

schema_name.name: schema_name
schema_name.description: Name of model expressed in schema; a 'schema' usually contains all of the packages of one 'model' of a publisher. A publisher with more than one model can have multiple schemas.

BMM_SCHEMA_STATE.name: BMM_SCHEMA_STATE
BMM_SCHEMA_STATE.description: Enumeration of processing states of a `BMM_SCHEMA` used by creation and validation routines in `BMM_SCHEMA`.

BMM_CONSTANT.name: BMM_CONSTANT
BMM_CONSTANT.description: An immutable, static value-returning element scoped to a class. The `_value_` is the result of the evaluation of the `_generator_`, which may be as simple as a literal value, or may be any expression, including a function call.

generator.name: generator
generator.description: Generator expression for the constant value. In the  degenerate case, this is just a literal value, but may also be any other expression valid in the context.

BMM_CONTAINER_PROPERTY.name: BMM_CONTAINER_PROPERTY
BMM_CONTAINER_PROPERTY.description: Meta-type of for properties of linear container type, such as List<T> etc.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_FUNCTION.name: BMM_FUNCTION
BMM_FUNCTION.description: A formal element with signature of the form: `name ({arg:TArg}*):TResult`. A function is a computed (rather than data) element, generally assumed to be non-state-changing.

operator_definition.name: operator_definition
operator_definition.description: Optional details enabling a function to be represented as an operator in a syntactic representation.

result.name: result
result.description: Automatically created Result variable, usable in body and post-condition.

BMM_OPERATOR.name: BMM_OPERATOR
BMM_OPERATOR.description: Definition of a symbolic operator associated with a function.

position.name: position
position.description: Position of operator in syntactic representation.

symbols.name: symbols
symbols.description: Set of `String` symbols that may be used to represent this operator in a textual representation of a BMM model.

name.name: name
name.description: Formal name of the operator, e.g. 'minus' etc.

BMM_PROPERTY.name: BMM_PROPERTY
BMM_PROPERTY.description: Meta-type of a property definition within a class definition of an object model. The `_is_composition_` attribute indicates whether the property has sub-part or an association semantics with respect to the owning class.

is_im_runtime.name: is_im_runtime
is_im_runtime.description: True if this property is marked with info model `_im_runtime_` property.

is_im_infrastructure.name: is_im_infrastructure
is_im_infrastructure.description: True if this property was marked with info model `_im_infrastructure_` flag.

is_composition.name: is_composition
is_composition.description: True if this property instance is a compositional sub-part of the owning class instance. Equivalent to 'composition' in UML associations (but missing from UML properties without associations) and also 'cascade-delete' semantics in ER schemas.

BMM_ROUTINE.name: BMM_ROUTINE
BMM_ROUTINE.description: A feature defining a routine, scoped to a class.

body.name: body
body.description: Body of a routine, i.e. executable program.

direction.name: direction
direction.description: Optional read/write direction of the parameter. If none-supplied, the parameter is treated as `in`, i.e. readable.

BMM_VARIABLE.name: BMM_VARIABLE
BMM_VARIABLE.description: A mutable entity whose scope is a routine.

scope.name: scope
scope.description: Routine within which variable is defined.

BMM_PROCEDURE.name: BMM_PROCEDURE
BMM_PROCEDURE.description: A formal element with signature of the form: `name ({arg:TArg}*)`. A procedure is a computed (rather than data) element, generally assumed to be state-changing.

BMM_UNITARY_PROPERTY.name: BMM_UNITARY_PROPERTY
BMM_UNITARY_PROPERTY.description: Meta-type of for properties of unitary type.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_CLASS_FEATURE.name: BMM_CLASS_FEATURE
BMM_CLASS_FEATURE.description: A class entity having a signature and a class as its scope.

scope.name: scope
scope.description: Class within which a referenceable element is known.

visibility.name: visibility
visibility.description: Visibility of this item to client entities.

BMM_INDEXED_CONTAINER_PROPERTY.name: BMM_INDEXED_CONTAINER_PROPERTY
BMM_INDEXED_CONTAINER_PROPERTY.description: Meta-type of for properties of linear container type, such as `Hash<Index_type, T>` etc.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_TYPED_FEATURE.name: BMM_TYPED_FEATURE
BMM_TYPED_FEATURE.description: A typed entity that is a feature within a context, and which may therefore be Void, i.e. 'nullable'.

is_nullable.name: is_nullable
is_nullable.description: True if this element can be null (Void) at execution time. May be interpreted as optionality in subtypes..

BMM_INSTANTIABLE.name: BMM_INSTANTIABLE
BMM_INSTANTIABLE.description: Meta-type representing instantiable features, i.e. features that are created as value objects.

BMM_CLASS_ENTITY.name: BMM_CLASS_ENTITY
BMM_CLASS_ENTITY.description: Any entity declared within a class.

is_synthesised_generic.name: is_synthesised_generic
is_synthesised_generic.description: True if this feature was synthesised due to generic substitution in an inherited type, or further constraining of a formal generic parameter.

BMM_RESULT.name: BMM_RESULT
BMM_RESULT.description: Automatically declared variable representing result instance of a Function call.

BMM_ROUTINE_BODY.name: BMM_ROUTINE_BODY
BMM_ROUTINE_BODY.description: Abstract ancestor of routine body meta-types.

BMM_ROUTINE_EXTERNAL.name: BMM_ROUTINE_EXTERNAL
BMM_ROUTINE_EXTERNAL.description: External routine placeholder, containing sufficient meta-data to enable a routine in an external library to be called.

meta_data.name: meta_data
meta_data.description: External call general meta-data, including target routine name, type mapping etc.

BMM_FEATURE_GROUP.name: BMM_FEATURE_GROUP
BMM_FEATURE_GROUP.description: A logical group of features, with a name and set of properties that applies to the group.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of this feature group; defaults to 'feature'.

properties.name: properties
properties.description: Set of properties of this group, represented as name/value pairs. These are understood to apply logically to all of the features contained within the group.

features.name: features
features.description: Set of features in this group.

visibility.name: visibility
visibility.description: Optional visibility to apply to all features in this group.

BMM_VISIBILITY.name: BMM_VISIBILITY
BMM_VISIBILITY.description:
Abstract parent of visibility representation.

TODO: define schemes; probably need to support C++/Java scheme as well as better type-based schemes.

BMM_OPERATOR_POSITION.name: BMM_OPERATOR_POSITION
BMM_OPERATOR_POSITION.description: Enumeration of possible position of operator in a syntactic representation for operators associated with 1- and 2- degree functions.

BMM_PARAMETER_DIRECTION.name: BMM_PARAMETER_DIRECTION
BMM_PARAMETER_DIRECTION.description: Enumeration of parameter read/write direction values.

BMM_INTEGER_VALUE.name: BMM_INTEGER_VALUE
BMM_INTEGER_VALUE.description: Meta-type for a literal Integer value, for which `_type_` is fixed to the `BMM_TYPE` representing `Integer` and `_value_` is of type `Integer`.

value.name: value
value.description: Native Integer value.

BMM_STRING_VALUE.name: BMM_STRING_VALUE
BMM_STRING_VALUE.description: Meta-type for a literal String value, for which `_type_` is fixed to the `BMM_TYPE` representing `String` and `_value_` is of type `String`.

value.name: value
value.description: Native String value.

BMM_LITERAL_VALUE.name: BMM_LITERAL_VALUE
BMM_LITERAL_VALUE.description: Meta-type for literal instance values declared in a model. Instance values may be inline values of primitive types in the usual fashion or complex objects in syntax form, e.g. JSON.

value_literal.name: value_literal
value_literal.description: A serial representation of the value.

value.name: value
value.description: A native representation of the value, possibly derived by deserialising `_value_literal_`.

syntax.name: syntax
syntax.description: Optional specification of formalism of the `_value_literal_` attribute for complex values. Value may be any of `json | yawl | xml | odin | rdf` or another value agreed by the user community. If not set, `json` is assumed.

BMM_BOOLEAN_VALUE.name: BMM_BOOLEAN_VALUE
BMM_BOOLEAN_VALUE.description: Meta-type for a literal Boolean value, for which `_type_` is fixed to the `BMM_TYPE` representing `Boolean` and `_value_` is of type `Boolean`.

value.name: value
value.description: Native Boolean value.

BMM_PRIMITIVE_VALUE.name: BMM_PRIMITIVE_VALUE
BMM_PRIMITIVE_VALUE.description: Meta-type for literals whose concrete type is a primitive type.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_CONTAINER_VALUE.name: BMM_CONTAINER_VALUE
BMM_CONTAINER_VALUE.description: Meta-type for literals whose concrete type is a linear container type, i.e. array, list or set.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_UNITARY_VALUE.name: BMM_UNITARY_VALUE
BMM_UNITARY_VALUE.description: Meta-type for literals whose concrete type is a unitary type in the BMM sense.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_INDEXED_CONTAINER_VALUE.name: BMM_INDEXED_CONTAINER_VALUE
BMM_INDEXED_CONTAINER_VALUE.description: Meta-type for literals whose concrete type is an indexed container, i.e. Hash table, Map etc.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_INTERVAL_VALUE.name: BMM_INTERVAL_VALUE
BMM_INTERVAL_VALUE.description: Meta-type for literal intervals of type `Interval<Ordered>`.

BMM_MODEL.name: BMM_MODEL
BMM_MODEL.description: Definition of the root of a BMM model (along with what is inherited from `BMM_SCHEMA_CORE`).

class_definitions.name: class_definitions
class_definitions.description: All classes in this model, keyed by type name.

used_models.name: used_models
used_models.description: List of other models 'used' (i.e. 'imported' by this model). Classes in the current model may refer to classes in a used model by specifying the other class's `_scope_` meta-attribute.

BMM_MODEL_METADATA.name: BMM_MODEL_METADATA
BMM_MODEL_METADATA.description: Core properties of `BMM_MODEL`, may be used in a serial representation as well, such as `P_BMM_SCHEMA`.

rm_publisher.name: rm_publisher
rm_publisher.description: Publisher of model expressed in the schema.

rm_release.name: rm_release
rm_release.description: Release of model expressed in the schema as a 3-part numeric, e.g. "3.1.0" .

BMM_PACKAGE.name: BMM_PACKAGE
BMM_PACKAGE.description:
Abstraction of a package as a tree structure whose nodes can contain other packages and classes.

The `_name_` may be qualified if it is a top-level package.

classes.name: classes
classes.description: Classes listed as being in this package.

BMM_PACKAGE_CONTAINER.name: BMM_PACKAGE_CONTAINER
BMM_PACKAGE_CONTAINER.description: A BMM model component that contains packages and classes.

packages.name: packages
packages.description: Child packages; keys all in upper case for guaranteed matching.

scope.name: scope
scope.description: Model element within which a referenceable element is known.

BMM_TYPED.name: BMM_TYPED
BMM_TYPED.description: Any entity that has a declared or inferred static type, and that can therefore be generate a value.

type.name: type
type.description: Declared or inferred static type of the entity.

BMM_DECLARATION.name: BMM_DECLARATION
BMM_DECLARATION.description: Meta-type of BMM declared model elements. A _declaration_ is a an element of a model _specified by an author within a model definition_ within a context, which defines the _scope_ of the element. Thus, a class definition and its property and routine definitions are model elements, but Types are not, since they are derived from model elements.

documentation.name: documentation
documentation.description:
Optional documentation of this element, as a keyed list.

It is strongly recommended to use the following key /type combinations for the relevant purposes:

* `"purpose": String`
* `"keywords": List<String>`
* `"use": String`
* `"misuse": String`
* `"references": String`

Other keys and value types may be freely added.

scope.name: scope
scope.description: Model element within which an element is declared.

extensions.name: extensions
extensions.description: Optional meta-data of this element, as a keyed list. May be used to extend the meta-model.

EL_EXPRESSION.name: EL_EXPRESSION
EL_EXPRESSION.description: Abstract parent of all typed expression meta-types.

EL_TERMINAL.name: EL_TERMINAL

EL_LITERAL.name: EL_LITERAL
EL_LITERAL.description: Literal value of any type known in the model, including primitive types. Defined via a `BMM_LITERAL_VALUE`.

value.name: value
value.description: The reference item from which the value of this node can be computed.

precedence_overridden.name: precedence_overridden
precedence_overridden.description: True if the natural precedence of operators is overridden in the expression represented by this node of the expression tree. If True, parentheses should be introduced around the totality of the syntax expression corresponding to this operator node and its operands.

symbol.name: symbol
symbol.description: The symbol actually used in the expression, or intended to be used for serialisation. Must be a member of `OPERATOR_DEF._symbols_`.

definition.name: definition
definition.description: Function equivalent to this operator, inferred by matching operator against functions defined in interface of principal operand.

EL_INSTANTIABLE_REF.name: EL_INSTANTIABLE_REF
EL_INSTANTIABLE_REF.description: Terminal item corresponding to a reference to a directly instantiable entity, i.e. a variable, constant, or property.

definition.name: definition
definition.description: Definition of the constant, property or variable, inferred by inspection of the current scoping instance.

EL_PREDICATE.name: EL_PREDICATE
EL_PREDICATE.description: Parent type of predicate of any object reference.

operand.name: operand
operand.description: The target instance of this predicate.

EL_DEFINED.name: EL_DEFINED
EL_DEFINED.description:
A predicate taking one external variable reference argument, that returns true if the reference is resolvable, i.e. the external value is obtainable.

NOTE: probably to be removed.

EL_FUNCTION_CALL.name: EL_FUNCTION_CALL
EL_FUNCTION_CALL.description: A call made on a closed function agent, returning a result. Equivalent to an 'application' of a function in Lambda calculus.

EL_AGENT_CALL.name: EL_AGENT_CALL
EL_AGENT_CALL.description: A call made to a 'closed' agent, i.e. one with no remaining open arguments.

EL_AGENT.name: EL_AGENT
EL_AGENT.description:
A delayed routine call, whose arguments may be open, partially closed or closed. Instances may include closed delayed calls like `calculate_age (dob="1987-09-13", today="2019-06-03")` but also partially open calls such as `format_structure (struct=?, style=3)`, where `struct` is an open argument.

Evaluation type (i.e. type of runtime evaluated form) is `BMM_SIGNATURE`.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of the routine being called.

closed_args.name: closed_args
closed_args.description: Closed arguments of a routine call as a tuple of objects.

open_args.name: open_args
open_args.description: Optional list of names of open arguments of the call. If not provided, and the `_name_` refers to a routine with more arguments than supplied in `_closed_args_`, the missing arguments are inferred from the `_definition_`.

definition.name: definition
definition.description: Reference to definition of a routine for which this is an agent, if one exists.

EL_TUPLE_ITEM.name: EL_TUPLE_ITEM
EL_TUPLE_ITEM.description: A single tuple item, with an optional name.

item.name: item
item.description: Reference to value entity. If Void, this indicates that the item in this position is Void, e.g. within a routine call parameter list.

EL_PROCEDURE_AGENT.name: EL_PROCEDURE_AGENT
EL_PROCEDURE_AGENT.description: An agent whose signature is of a procedure, i.e. has no result type.

definition.name: definition
definition.description: Reference to definition of routine for which this is a call instance.

EL_TUPLE.name: EL_TUPLE
EL_TUPLE.description: Defines an array of optionally named items each of any type.

items.name: items
items.description: Items in the tuple, potentially with names. Typical use is to represent an argument list to routine call.

type.name: type
type.description: Static type inferred from literal value.

EL_FUNCTION_AGENT.name: EL_FUNCTION_AGENT
EL_FUNCTION_AGENT.description: An agent whose signature is of a function, i.e. has a result type.

definition.name: definition
definition.description: Reference to definition of a routine for which this is a direct call instance, if one exists.

EL_ATTACHED.name: EL_ATTACHED
EL_ATTACHED.description: A predicate on any object reference (including function call) that returns True if the reference is attached, i.e. non-Void.

EL_INSTANCE_REF.name: EL_INSTANCE_REF
EL_INSTANCE_REF.description: A reference to an instance of any kind.

EL_SELF_REF.name: EL_SELF_REF
EL_SELF_REF.description: Special meta-type used to represent a reference that may appear in any routine, pre- or post-condition, or invariant, and resolves to the current object within which feature references are scoped; corresponds to 'self', 'this' or 'Current' in various programming languages.

type.name: type
type.description: Type of the current scoping instance, inferred from expression context.

EL_TYPE_REF.name: EL_TYPE_REF
EL_TYPE_REF.description:
Meta-type for reference to a non-abstract type as an object. Assumed to be accessible at run-time. Typically represented syntactically as `TypeName` or `{TypeName}`.

May be used as a value, or as the qualifier for a function or constant access.

type.name: type
type.description: Type, directly from the name of the reference, e.g. `{SOME_TYPE}`.

EL_SCOPED_REF.name: EL_SCOPED_REF
EL_SCOPED_REF.description: A reference that is scoped by a containing entity and requires a context qualifier if it is not the currently scoping entity.

scope.name: scope
scope.description: Reference to an owning object for this terminal element, if it is not the current scope.

EL_CONDITIONAL_EXPRESSION.name: EL_CONDITIONAL_EXPRESSION
EL_CONDITIONAL_EXPRESSION.description: Conditional structure used in condition chain expressions. Evaluated by evaluating its `_condition_`, which is a Boolean-returning expression, and if this returns True, the result is the evaluation result of `_expression_`.

condition.name: condition
condition.description: Gate expression that acts as the condition under which the target `_expression_` is returned.

EL_CONDITION_CHAIN.name: EL_CONDITION_CHAIN
EL_CONDITION_CHAIN.description:
Compound expression consisting of a chain of condition-gated expressions, and an ungated `_else_` member that as a whole, represents an if/then/elseif/else chains.

Evaluated by iterating through `_items_` and for each one, evaluating its `_condition_`, which if True, causes the evaluation result of the chain to be that item's `_result_` evaluation result.

If no member of `_items_` has a True-returning `_condition_`, the evaluation result is the result of evaluating the `_else_` expression.

items.name: items
items.description: Members of the chain, equivalent to branches in an if/then/else chain and cases in a case statement.

EL_CONSTRAINED.name: EL_CONSTRAINED
EL_CONSTRAINED.description: Abstract parent for second-order or constrained forms of first-order expression meta-types.

base_expression.name: base_expression
base_expression.description: The base expression of this constrained form.

EL_CASE_TABLE.name: EL_CASE_TABLE
EL_CASE_TABLE.description:
Compound expression consisting of a list of value-range / expression pairs, and an  `_else_` member that as a whole, represents a case statement flavour of decision table.

Evaluated by iterating through `_items_` and for each one, comparing `_input_` to the item `_value_range_`. If the `_input_` is in the range, the evaluation result of the table is that item's `_result_` evaluation result. 

If no member of `_items_` has a True-returning `_condition_`, the evaluation result is the result of evaluating the `_else_` expression.

items.name: items
items.description: Members of the chain, equivalent to branches in an if/then/else chain and cases in a case statement.

input.name: input
input.description: Input value that is compared against each `_items_[i]._value_range_` to determine the overall result.

EL_DECISION_TABLE.name: EL_DECISION_TABLE
EL_DECISION_TABLE.description: Complex expression structure representing a logical decision table.

else.name: else
else.description: Result expression of the chain if no member of `_items_` succeeds in evaluation.

items.name: items
items.description: Members of the chain, equivalent to branches in an if/then/else chain and cases in a case statement.

result.name: result
result.description: Result expression of conditional, if its `_condition_` evaluates to True.

EL_SIMPLE.name: EL_SIMPLE
EL_SIMPLE.description: Simple expression type that may be used in other simple expressions.

BMM_CONDITIONAL_ACTION.name: BMM_CONDITIONAL_ACTION
BMM_CONDITIONAL_ACTION.description: Conditional, or 'gated' statement, consisting of a Boolean-returning `_condition_` and the target `_statement_`.

condition.name: condition
condition.description: The gate condition for the target statement.

BMM_ASSIGNMENT.name: BMM_ASSIGNMENT
BMM_ASSIGNMENT.description: Statement type representing an assignment from a value-generating source to a writable entity, i.e. a variable reference or property.

target.name: target
target.description: The target variable on the notional left-hand side of this assignment.

source.name: source
source.description: Source right hand side) of the assignment.

BMM_ASSERTION.name: BMM_ASSERTION
BMM_ASSERTION.description:
A statement that asserts the truth of its expression. If not, generates an exception (depending on run-time settings).

May be rendered in syntax as `assert condition` or similar.

tag.name: tag
tag.description: Optional tag, typically used to designate design intention of the assertion, e.g. `"Inv_all_members_valid"`.

BMM_PROCEDURE_CALL.name: BMM_PROCEDURE_CALL
BMM_PROCEDURE_CALL.description: A call made on a closed procedure agent.

BMM_STATEMENT_ITEM.name: BMM_STATEMENT_ITEM
BMM_STATEMENT_ITEM.description: Abstract parent of statement types representing a locally defined routine body.

BMM_STATEMENT.name: BMM_STATEMENT
BMM_STATEMENT.description: Abstract parent of 'statement' types that may be defined to implement BMM Routines.

BMM_STATEMENT_BLOCK.name: BMM_STATEMENT_BLOCK
BMM_STATEMENT_BLOCK.description: A statement 'block' corresponding to the programming language concept of the same name. May be used to establish scope in specific languages.

items.name: items
items.description: Child blocks of the current block.

BMM_SIMPLE_STATEMENT.name: BMM_SIMPLE_STATEMENT
BMM_SIMPLE_STATEMENT.description: Simple statement, i.e. statement with one logical element - a single expression, procedure call etc.

BMM_DEFINITIONS.name: BMM_DEFINITIONS
BMM_DEFINITIONS.description: Definitions used by all BMM packages.

Bmm_internal_version.name: Bmm_internal_version
Bmm_internal_version.description: Current internal version of BMM meta-model, used to determine if a given schema can be processed by a given implementation of the model.

Schema_name_delimiter.name: Schema_name_delimiter

P_BMM_CLASS.name: P_BMM_CLASS
P_BMM_CLASS.description: Definition of persistent form of `BMM_CLASS` for serialisation to ODIN, JSON, XML etc.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of the class. Persisted attribute.

ancestors.name: ancestors
ancestors.description: List of immediate inheritance parents. If there are generic ancestors, use `_ancestor_defs_` instead. Persisted attribute.

properties.name: properties
properties.description: List of attributes defined in this class. Persistent attribute.

is_abstract.name: is_abstract
is_abstract.description: True if this is an abstract type. Persisted attribute.

is_override.name: is_override
is_override.description: True if this class definition overrides one found in an included schema.

generic_parameter_defs.name: generic_parameter_defs
generic_parameter_defs.description: List of generic parameter definitions. Persisted attribute.

source_schema_id.name: source_schema_id
source_schema_id.description: Reference to original source schema defining this class. Set during `BMM_SCHEMA` materialise. Useful for GUI tools to enable user to edit the schema file containing a given class (i.e. taking into account that a class may be in any of the schemas in a schema inclusion hierarchy).

uid.name: uid
uid.description: Unique id generated for later comparison during merging, in order to detect if two classes are the same. Assigned in post-load processing.

ancestor_defs.name: ancestor_defs
ancestor_defs.description: List of structured inheritance ancestors, used only in the case of generic inheritance. Persisted attribute.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of this property within its class. Persisted attribute.

is_mandatory.name: is_mandatory
is_mandatory.description: True if this property is mandatory in its class. Persisted attribute.

is_computed.name: is_computed
is_computed.description: True if this property is computed rather than stored in objects of this class. Persisted Attribute.

is_im_infrastructure.name: is_im_infrastructure
is_im_infrastructure.description: True if this property is info model 'infrastructure' rather than 'data'. Persisted attribute.

is_im_runtime.name: is_im_runtime
is_im_runtime.description: True if this property is info model 'runtime' settable property. Persisted attribute.

type_def.name: type_def
type_def.description: Type definition of this property, if not a simple String type reference. Persisted attribute.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of the parameter, e.g. 'T' etc. Persisted attribute. Name is limited to 1 character, upper case.

conforms_to_type.name: conforms_to_type
conforms_to_type.description: Optional conformance constraint - the name of a type to which a concrete substitution of this generic parameter must conform. Persisted attribute.

container_type.name: container_type
container_type.description: The type of the container. This converts to the `_root_type_` in `BMM_GENERIC_TYPE`. Persisted attribute.

type_def.name: type_def
type_def.description: Type definition of `_type_`, if not a simple String type reference. Persisted attribute.

type.name: type
type.description: The target type; this converts to the first parameter in `_generic_parameters_` in `BMM_GENERIC_TYPE`. Persisted attribute.

type.name: type
type.description: Name of type - must be a simple class name.

type.name: type
type.description: Simple type parameter as a single letter like 'T', 'G' etc.

root_type.name: root_type
root_type.description: Root type of this generic type, e.g. `Interval` in `Interval<Integer>`.

generic_parameter_defs.name: generic_parameter_defs
generic_parameter_defs.description: Generic parameters of the root_type in this type specifier if non-simple types. The order must match the order of the owning class's formal generic parameter declarations. Persistent attribute.

generic_parameters.name: generic_parameters
generic_parameters.description: Generic parameters of the `_root_type_` in this type specifier, if simple types. The order must match the order of the owning class's formal generic parameter declarations. Persistent attribute.

P_BMM_PACKAGE.name: P_BMM_PACKAGE
P_BMM_PACKAGE.description: Persisted form of a package as a tree structure whose nodes can contain more packages and/or classes.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of the package from schema; this name may be qualified if it is a top-level package within the schema, or unqualified. Persistent attribute.

classes.name: classes
classes.description: List of classes in this package. Persistent attribute.

P_BMM_PACKAGE_CONTAINER.name: P_BMM_PACKAGE_CONTAINER
P_BMM_PACKAGE_CONTAINER.description: Persisted form of a model component that contains packages.

packages.name: packages
packages.description: Package structure as a hierarchy of packages each potentially containing names of classes in that package in the original model.

cardinality.name: cardinality
cardinality.description: Cardinality of this property in its class. Persistent attribute.

type_def.name: type_def
type_def.description: Type definition of this property, if not a simple String type reference. Persistent attribute.

type.name: type
type.description: If the type is a simple type, then this attribute will hold the type name. If the type is a container or generic, then type_ref will hold the type definition. The resulting type is generated in type_def.

type_ref.name: type_ref
type_ref.description: Type definition of this property computed from `_type_` for later use in `_bmm_property_`.

type_ref.name: type_ref
type_ref.description: Type definition of this property computed from `_type_` for later use in `_bmm_property_`.

type.name: type
type.description: Type definition of this property, if a simple String type reference. Really we should use `_type_def_` to be regular in the schema, but that makes the schema more wordy and less clear. So we use this persisted String value, and compute the `_type_def_` on the fly. Persisted attribute.

type_def.name: type_def
type_def.description: Type definition of this property, if not a simple String type reference. Persistent attribute.

P_BMM_ENUMERATION_INTEGER.name: P_BMM_ENUMERATION_INTEGER
P_BMM_ENUMERATION_INTEGER.description: Persistent form of an instance of `BMM_ENUMERATION_INTEGER`.

id.name: id
id.description: Full identifier of the included schema, e.g. `"openehr_primitive_types_1.0.2"`.
